<subSubSection id="7E83FE90F870FF9FFF378CF8746FF9F3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3626AD1BF870FF9FFF378CF87079FA3D" blockId="20.[189,310,1427,1453]" box="[189,310,1427,1453]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading id="6D6E1A77F870FF9FFF378CF87079FA3D" bold="true" box="[189,310,1427,1453]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis id="04ED7109F870FF9FFF378CF87079FA3D" bold="true" box="[189,310,1427,1453]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3626AD1BF870FF9FFF378CA2746FF9F3" blockId="20.[188,1398,1481,1635]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Recognized by the following characters: Total length 5.5–6.3; antennal segment II dark brown, subequal to head width; anterior part of body broadly reddish, head, pronotum and scutellum bright reddish, base of hemelytron reddish at level with apex of scutellum, remainder bluish black (
<figureCitation id="AEA2B19EF870FF9FFBEE8F75758CF9A8" box="[1124,1219,1566,1592]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="49.[189,232,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[277,1345,291,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-12@49.[189,1398,265,1811]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="Fig. 8. Dorsal view, male genitalia and label data of type specimens for Mertila spp. A–C. Mertila bhamo Stonedahl, 1988, holotype, AMNH_PBI 00342529, NHM. D–E. Mertila malayensis Distant, 1904, ♂, lectotype, NHMUK010096278, NHM. F. Mertila malayensis Distant, 1904, paralectotype, AMNH_PBI 00342600, NHM. G. Mertila sarawak Stonedahl,1988, holotype, ♂, NHMUK010096279, NHM. H. Mertila sarawak Stonedahl, 1988, paratype, AMNH_PBI 00342601, NHM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690380/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
); tibiae brown; genital capsule dorsally with two strongly twisted, tapering, hollow tubular processes (
<figureCitation id="AEA2B19EF870FF9FFB3C8F22745CF9F3" box="[1206,1299,1609,1635]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="49.[189,232,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[277,1345,291,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-12@49.[189,1398,265,1811]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="Fig. 8. Dorsal view, male genitalia and label data of type specimens for Mertila spp. A–C. Mertila bhamo Stonedahl, 1988, holotype, AMNH_PBI 00342529, NHM. D–E. Mertila malayensis Distant, 1904, ♂, lectotype, NHMUK010096278, NHM. F. Mertila malayensis Distant, 1904, paralectotype, AMNH_PBI 00342600, NHM. G. Mertila sarawak Stonedahl,1988, holotype, ♂, NHMUK010096279, NHM. H. Mertila sarawak Stonedahl, 1988, paratype, AMNH_PBI 00342601, NHM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690380/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
